<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-6217] replace doesn&apos;t clean up system.peers if you have a new IP</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-6217</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When you use replace_token (or replace_node or replace_address) if the new node has a different IP, the old node will still be in system.peers&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12674536">CASSANDRA-6217</key>
            <summary>replace doesn&apos;t clean up system.peers if you have a new IP</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=21133&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Bug</type>
